<title>FRANCE: Total unit invests in the United States.</title>
<headline>Total unit invests in the United States.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>French oil group Total said on Wednesday its Cray Valley unit had acquired the castor oil and polyethilene wax business of U.S. company Southern Clay Products (SCP)/Laporte for an undisclosed amount.</p>
<p>Cray Valley is part of Total's resins division. The acquisition will strengthen its position in the field of rheological additives used in decorative and industrial coatings as well as in printing inks, the statement said.</p>
<p>Cray Valley will market the new products worldwide, with the exception of the United States, which is covered by Cook Composites and Polymers (CCP), a sister company of Cray Valley.</p>
